10/11/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A two-day meeting of the Adriatic Charter signatories starts Friday (12 November) in Croatia. 
The foreign ministry says delegations from NATO, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Greece, Hungary, Italy, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro, Slovenia and Turkey will also attend. 
Participants will discuss issues of regional co-operation as well as integration reforms. 
(HINA, HRT - 09/11/04)
